From 99eda1bdceac0c7035b0fe2b17be272f6f6e59df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jithender Kondam <jreddy@marvell.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Sep 2025 09:55:19 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Remove stale PFC status entries from m_portPfcStatus when a
 port is deleted from the PORT_QOS_MAP table.

Why I did it:
Previously, when a port was deleted from the PORT_QOS_MAP table, the
m_portPfcStatus map could retain stale information about the port's PFC
(Priority Flow Control) status. This could lead to inconsistencies in
buffer management, as the system might attempt to use outdated PFC
status for ports that no longer exist or have been reconfigured. This
could happen when CABLE_LENGTH for the port is set.

How I did it
By erasing the port's entry from m_portPfcStatus upon receiving a delete
command, the fix ensures that the internal state accurately reflects the
current configuration, preventing potential misconfigurations or
resource leaks.

How to verify it
TBD

Which release branch to backport (provide reason below if selected)
202505
